+From a0dff99fb6b03a8d4e601b27d7609a2dbbc96a8e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
+From: sarabjeets <sarabjeets@marvell.com>
+Date: Thu, 19 Mar 2026 12:01:19 +0530
+Subject: [PATCH] BFD Tx/Rx intervals not updating, even with Polling complete
+MIME-Version: 1.0
+Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
+Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit
+
+As per RFC-5880, section 6.8.3 requires a higher DesiredMinTxInterval in UP
+state to be deferred only until the local Poll Sequence terminates. From section
+6.5, that happens when the poll initiator receives a packet with the Final bit
+set. Since bs_final_handler() is invoked both for local-poll completion and
+while responding to a peer Poll, the defer logic must be conditioned on
+bs->polling as well (currently this is not happening), not just on
+(ses_state == Up && new > old). Otherwise the new interval is incorrectly
+suppressed even after poll completion. This also conflicts with section 6.8.3’s
+rule that all other timing changes take effect immediately and section 6.8.7’s
+requirement to recalculate tx interval as
+max(DesiredMinTxInterval, RemoteMinRxInterval).
+
+Refer to the below table for different scenarios which are encountered.
+
+Scenario	                                            Polling	                              Effect
+--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
+Call site 1 (our poll done, F received)	           0 (cleared before call)	      Condition false → applies new timer
+Call site 2 (peer's poll, our poll done)	   0	                              Condition false → applies new timer
+Call site 2 (peer's poll, our poll still active)   1	                              If increasing, defers → correct per RFC
+Down→Up transition, F received	                   0 (cleared before call)	      Applies configured timer → fixes the original bug
+
+Signed-off-by: sarabjeets <sarabjeets@marvell.com>
+---
+ bfdd/bfd.c | 2 +-
+ 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)
+
+diff --git a/bfdd/bfd.c b/bfdd/bfd.c
+index d9514ab5a..305e1c37b 100644
+--- a/bfdd/bfd.c
++++ b/bfdd/bfd.c
+@@ -1470,7 +1470,7 @@ void bs_final_handler(struct bfd_session *bs)
+ 		bs->xmt_TO = bs->remote_timers.required_min_rx;
+ 	
+ 	/* Only apply increased transmission interval after Poll Sequence */
+-	if (bs->ses_state == PTM_BFD_UP && bs->xmt_TO > old_xmt_TO) {
++	if (bs->polling && bs->ses_state == PTM_BFD_UP && bs->xmt_TO > old_xmt_TO) {
+ 		bs->xmt_TO = old_xmt_TO;  /* Keep old timing until Poll Sequence done */
+ 		return;
+ 	}
